"Muhammad ibn Ziyad reported: Wahb ibn Munabbih, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cWhoever places his lusts beneath his feet, Satan will flee from his shadow. Whoever overcomes his whims by his forbearance, that one is among the victorious scholars.\u201d Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304\u2019 4\/60 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0632\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25043,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/07\/11\/saeed-on-forbearance-real-man\/","url_meta":{"origin":24158,"position":1},"title":"Sa\u2019id on Hilm: A real man does not disparage others","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 11, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Dunya reported: Sa\u2019id ibn al-\u2018As, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cI have not insulted a man ever since I became a man.\u201d Source: al-H\u0323ilm li-Ibn Abi\u0304 Dunya\u0304 119 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0635\u0650 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0634\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0645\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u0627 \u0645\u064f\u0646\u0652\u0630\u064f \u0643\u064f\u0646\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u0627 119 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0644\u0645\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":43872,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/07\/03\/noah-forgive-my-people\/","url_meta":{"origin":24158,"position":2},"title":"Nuh on Patience: Forgive my people for they do not know","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 3, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubayd ibn \u2018Umayr reported: They used to beat and strangle Noah, upon him be peace, until he fainted. When he woke up, Noah said, \u201cO Allah, forgive my people for they do not know.\u201d Source: Tafsi\u0304r Ibn Abi\u0304 H\u0323a\u0304tim 7:59 Al-Qadi \u2018Iyad commented, \u201cA similar statement was narrated from our\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35393,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/03\/16\/abu-darda-sabr\/","url_meta":{"origin":24158,"position":3},"title":"Abu Darda on Patience: Be forbearing in the face of insults, curses","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 16, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdur Rahman ibn Jubayr reported: Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cGive up your reputation for the sake of Allah. Whoever abuses you, insults you, or fights you, leave him to Allah. If you do a bad deed, then ask forgiveness from Allah.\u201d Source: Ta\u0304ri\u0304kh Dimashq 47\/180\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":43359,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/22\/keep-reward-insulter\/","url_meta":{"origin":24158,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Forbearance: Keep your reward from the insulter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 22, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Sulaym reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf a man insults you and reviles you for something he knows about you, do not disparage him for something you know about him. You will have his reward and he will have his sin, so do\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34059,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/03\/22\/hilm-must-be-learned\/","url_meta":{"origin":24158,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Hilm: Forbearance must be learned and cultivated","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 22, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, knowledge only comes by learning and forbearance only comes by cultivating forbearance. Whoever aims for good will receive goodness and whoever seeks to evade evil will be protected from it.\u201d Source: Ta\u0304ri\u0304kh Baghda\u0304d 9\/129 Grade: Hasan (fair)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadith